<subSubSection id="AF32BEA3CC040A89C91953AEBF333DE8" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CC56408E8CED13B4532C419F486BA9C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="34258ECF6CF69DF70BAD90AB78613776" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">
<taxonomicName id="8A4DC4585040C2F2276AED07F17D4490" authorityName="Kang" authorityYear="2022" class="Insecta" family="Braconidae" genus="Retusigaster" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Retusigaster vanduzeei" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vanduzeei">
<emphasis id="FBE855B46702C9FA2617790DFC0080A0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">Retusigaster vanduzeei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="BC3FF85800F3F50F8F797BE4D57511F5" class="Insecta" genus="R." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="R. noguerai" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="noguerai">
<emphasis id="93D3F46157E682B49D3A3C044910DCFE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">R. noguerai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mercado. Using the following characters, the members of 
<taxonomicName id="46C76C30091C38928C950D87FFE45834" class="Insecta" genus="R." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="R. vanduzeei" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="vanduzeei">
<emphasis id="3DF33BB343EA722965F7322669D52A0B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">R. vanduzeei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. nov. can be distinguished from other members the genus: inner and outer orbits orange (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="865755FCD6B23E7CB403E026CFBAAC6C" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Retusigaster vanduzeei sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal head E lateral head F wings G mesopleuron and metapleuron H scutellum to T 3." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668122" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">5A-E</figureCitation>
); fore wing entirely infuscate (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="6708F5056595001FA5EF8957D8EF34BF" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Retusigaster vanduzeei sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal head E lateral head F wings G mesopleuron and metapleuron H scutellum to T 3." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668122" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">5F</figureCitation>
); precoxal sulcus crenulate nearly reaching posterior margin (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="B199E3546C0A35D0634025B8A438D539" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Retusigaster vanduzeei sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal head E lateral head F wings G mesopleuron and metapleuron H scutellum to T 3." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668122" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">5G</figureCitation>
); propodeal areola oval (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="28E119EE1E46F16E5D7929970D984779" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Retusigaster vanduzeei sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal head E lateral head F wings G mesopleuron and metapleuron H scutellum to T 3." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668122" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">5H</figureCitation>
); metasoma entirely dark (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="0AE545570616766BD128DE642E61E2DC" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Retusigaster vanduzeei sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal head E lateral head F wings G mesopleuron and metapleuron H scutellum to T 3." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668122" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">5B</figureCitation>
); T1 antero-laterally crenulate and postero-laterally slightly rugulose; T2 ~ 0.27 
<normalizedToken id="8D58AB55C8CA42394A7EAAE32F6F3037" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
longer than its posterior width (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="F6C4AD5009D8BF50597A5BB3037F7483" captionStart="Figure 5" captionStartId="F5" captionText="Figure 5. Retusigaster vanduzeei sp. nov. A lateral habitus B dorsal habitus C anterior head D dorsal head E lateral head F wings G mesopleuron and metapleuron H scutellum to T 3." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668122" pageId="0" pageNumber="47">5B, H</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="0588F6DE64D038F5B7B836EECAC9940F" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1092.80560.figure5" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/668122" pageId="0" pageNumber="47" start="Figure 5" startId="F5">
